unittitle.value: Hisham Khatib Collection - S.S. Luetzow Travelogue

extent.value: One album with string ties, containing 49 pages. Eight postcards and ship menus, forty gelatin silver photographs.

p.value: A photographic travelogue of a voyage taken on the S.S. Luetzow, second oriental cruise run by Norddeutscher Lloyd Bremen in April and May 1930. Part of the larger Hisham Khatib Collection.

Part of the Hisham Khatib Collection which contains 2,930 photographs and postcards (both individual prints and contained within albums) focussed on the Near East, including the Holy Land, Palestine, Jordan, Turkey, Syria and Egypt as well as a very small number from Europe.
